 Capt. Khanyisile Zwane, local police spokesperson, said that several Toyota Hilux bakkies were stolen in recent weeks. Older models are also at risk, Capt. Zwane warned. She advised vehicle owners to install extra security measures, park in safe areas and to regularly check on your parked vehicle where possible. Residents are also urged to report suspicious activity, persons or vehicles to the police.     The ferals need help #TrafficAlert: R555 closed, seven die in horrific crash Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za